When behavioral strategies alone are not sufficient to keep patients and staff safe, pharmacologic management is necessary. Of note, there are no FDA approved treatments for delirium and to our knowledge, there is no literature reviewing management of agitation in COVID-19. The recommendations below are for off-label use (Table 1
). They have been extrapolated from SARS and MERS literature, and reflect the general practice patterns of the Consultation-Liaison Psychiatry COVID-19 Delirium Workgroup at Massachusetts General Hospital. Figure 2
outlines a potential management algorithm for COVID-19 delirium.
